# WHY disintegration/imaging IS A DISTINCTIVE AXIS-40
# CONTINUATION:
#
#   github.com/disintegration/imaging by Grigory Dryapak
#   is the de-facto Go image-processing package — the
#   "pure-Go higher-level image manipulation layer" that
#   sits on top of the Go stdlib's `image` package
#   (which provides raw codec decode + pixel access but
#   no operations like resize/crop/blur).  Distinguishing
#   characteristics:
#     1. PURE-GO — zero CGo, zero C-library
#        dependencies; cross-compiles to any GOOS/GOARCH
#        without C-toolchain setup.  This is the
#        defining property that pigo exploits
#     2. RESIZE + RESAMPLING — `imaging.Resize(img,
#        w, h, imaging.Lanczos)` with multiple
#        resampling kernels (NearestNeighbor, Box,
#        Linear, Hermite, MitchellNetravali, CatmullRom,
#        BSpline, Gaussian, Bartlett, Lanczos,
#        Hann, Hamming, Blackman, Welch, Cosine)
#     3. ROTATE / FLIP / TRANSPOSE — `imaging.Rotate90`,
#        `imaging.FlipH`, `imaging.FlipV`,
#        `imaging.Transpose`, `imaging.Rotate(img,
#        angle, fillColor)` for arbitrary-angle rotation
#     4. COLOR ADJUSTMENT — `imaging.AdjustBrightness`,
#        `imaging.AdjustContrast`, `imaging.AdjustSaturation`,
#        `imaging.AdjustGamma`, `imaging.AdjustSigmoid`,
#        `imaging.Grayscale`, `imaging.Invert`
#     5. CONVOLUTION OPERATIONS — `imaging.Blur`,
#        `imaging.Sharpen`, `imaging.Convolve3x3`,
#        `imaging.Convolve5x5`
#     6. CROP + FIT + FILL — `imaging.CropAnchor`,
#        `imaging.Fit`, `imaging.Fill` with anchor-
#        point control (center, top-left, etc.)
#     7. EXIF-AWARE LOADING — `imaging.Open(path,
#        imaging.AutoOrientation(true))` reads JPEG
#        EXIF orientation tag + automatically rotates;
#        critical for mobile photos that frequently
#        embed non-default orientation
#     8. EXTENSIVE TEST COVERAGE — large unit-test
#        suite ensuring resampling + convolution
#        operations match reference implementations
#     9. ~5,500+ STARS ON disintegration/imaging
#    10. CRATES.IO-EQUIVALENT DOMINANCE — by-far the
#        most-depended-on Go image package outside the
#        standard library; used by pigo (this
#        completion), agnivade/shimmer, lmorg/murex,
#        bbkane/enventory, mrusme/gomphotherium,
#        cathedral-bot, qor-example, hexya-erp, and
#        thousands of other Go projects
